### creating encrypted files ###
ansible-vault create --help

# password prompt method
ansible-vault create secrets.yml
(ansible will prompt for a password to use to encrypt the file it creates for you)

# password file method
first create a password file that can be referenced:
echo "my long password" > password_file
ansible-vault create --vault-password-file password_file secrets.yml

# password script method
This is useful if wanting to store a password on a cetnral system for storing credentials
create a file to output to STDOUT with a password:
#!/bin/sh
echo "password"
chod +x password.sh
ansible-vault create --vault-password-file secrets.yml
